GNU C Library (glibc)
=====================

The GNU C Library (glibc) is the standard C library used by the
runtime VM. synthmodem redistributes a subset of the compiled
glibc shared libraries — `ld-linux.so.2`, `libc.so.6`, and
`libm.so.6` — at `vm/libc/`, sourced from the Debian bookworm
binary package `libc6` (glibc 2.36-9+deb12u13, i386).

These libraries are loaded inside the QEMU guest and linked
dynamically against the in-VM helpers (`d-modem`, `modemd-ctrl`,
`modemd-tunnel`, `slmodemd`, `pjsip-test-peer`). They are used
only when the slmodemd-pjsip backend is active (or during the
slmodemd-pjsip phase of the auto backend); the native backend
runs entirely on the host Node.js runtime and does not load them.

Upstream project:  https://www.gnu.org/software/libc/
Upstream source:   https://sourceware.org/git/glibc.git
Debian package:    https://packages.debian.org/bookworm/libc6

